<TITLE> Warid strikes deal with 3 IGW operators </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jul 5 (bdnews24.com) Warid Telecom, a subsidiary of UAE-based Abu Dhabi Group, has signed separate agreements with three International Gateway (IGW) operators for routing international calls to and from its network, a press release said. The CEO of Warid Telecom Muneer Farooqui and the CEOs and MDs of the three IGW -- Mir Telecom, Bangla Trac Communications Limited and NovoTel  signed the deal in the capital on July 2. The agreements came in compliance with the ILDTS (International Long Distance Telecommunications Services) policy 2007 and directives of BTRC, which made it mandatory for all mobile operators to establish a physical and logical interconnection with IGW operators for routing both international outgoing and incoming calls, the release said. The Bangladesh Telecommunications Regulatory Commission (BTRC) earlier granted licences to four IGW operators including BTCL to handle all international voice calls of all ANS operators. Warid Telecom launched its commercial operation in Bangladesh on May 10, 2007, with Next Generation Network technology to all the 64 districts in the count
